verbs.description: [V: s] i doctor springs into action at nyc marathon revives unconscious woman dr theodore strange was right on pace to finish his 25th new york city marathon in about four hours on sunday but then the unthinkable happened strange heard someone screaming help strange was just coming off of the queensboro bridge when his instincts took over he immediately went over to the voice and found a woman on the ground unconscious her friend had been calling out for help strange acted quickly asking a volunteer to lift the woman legs suspecting that she had passed out due to the strain of running the marathon she was losing her color and she was foaming at the mouth said strange who is vice chairman of primary care at northwell health and vice president of medical operations at staten island university hospital in prince bay he quickly checked her pulse and she did n’t have any he said strange a doctor of internal and geriatric medicine immediately began administering cpr nypd fdny and ems workers sprung into action clearing the area around strange and assisting him in aiding the woman they were wonderful strange said after receiving a defibrillator strange and emergency workers diligently attempted to revive the woman to woman dr theodore strange doctor nyc dr theodore strange
